10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 698.4 of Title 70, unless there
13 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 A. As used in this section, “eligible school district” means a
15 public school district or public school district foundation in this
16 state that has established a program to provide tuition or loan
17 repayment assistance to school district employees who pursue an
18 undergraduate degree from a teacher preparation program accredited
19 by the Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability leading
20 to a standard teaching certificate.
21 B. There is hereby created the Grow Your Own Educator Program
22 to provide matching fund grants to eligible school districts. The
23 program shall be established and maintained by the Office of
24 Educational Quality and Accountability.
