1 C. An eligible school district seeking to participate in the
2 Grow Your Own Educator Program shall submit an application in the
3 manner and on a form prescribed by the Office of Educational Quality
4 and Accountability. The application shall include:
5 1. The amount of matching fund grants requested;
6 2. The position of the employee pursuing an undergraduate
7 degree from a teacher preparation program; and
8 3. The subject area in which the employee is pursuing an
9 undergraduate degree from a teacher preparation program.
10 D. Matching fund grants shall be awarded on a first-come,
11 first-served basis. Grants shall be provided without any limitation
12 other than the amount of funds available in the Grow Your Own
13 Educator Revolving Fund created pursuant to Section 2 of this act
14 and the number of eligible school districts that apply.
15 E. By June 30, 2026, and each June 30 thereafter, an eligible
16 school district that receives a matching fund grant pursuant to this
17 section shall electronically submit a report to the Office of
18 Educational Quality and Accountability that includes:
19 1. A status update on the progress the employee receiving
20 tuition assistance is making in the teacher preparation program in
21 which he or she is enrolled; or
22 2. The employment status of the employee receiving loan
23 repayment assistance.
