12 received an undergraduate degree; and
13 4. The information submitted pursuant to subsection E of this
14 section.
15 G. The Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability
16 shall promulgate rules to implement the provisions of this section.
17 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 698.5 of Title 70, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
21 for the Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability to be
22 designated the “Grow Your Own Educator Revolving Fund”. The fund
23 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
24 and shall consist of all monies received by the Commission for
